# grout daemon arguments. `-t` = test-mode (no hugepages), suitable for the
# lab/MVP path and for running inside the CRA netns without host DPDK tuning.
# For a production fast path clear `-t` after preparing hugepages + vfio-pci.
# `-m 666` makes /run/grout.sock world-rw so FRR's dplane_grout (unprivileged
# `frr` user) can drive grout's EVPN fdb/FIB; without it zebra logs
# "Permission denied" and never syncs grout's interfaces/routes.
ARGS="-t -m 666"
